{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":640,"text":"In terms of invention,"},{"time":1880,"text":"I'd like to tell you the tale\nof one of my favorite projects."},{"time":4762,"text":"I think it's one of the most exciting\nthat I'm working on,"},{"time":8080,"text":"but I think it's also the simplest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10160,"text":"It's a project that has the potential\nto make a huge impact around the world."},{"time":14640,"text":"It addresses one of the biggest\nhealth issues on the planet,"},{"time":18080,"text":"the number one cause of death\nin children under five."},{"time":21640,"text":"Which is ...?"},{"time":23680,"text":"Water-borne diseases?\nDiarrhea? Malnutrition?"},{"time":27200,"text":"No."},{"time":28880,"text":"It's breathing the smoke\nfrom indoor cooking fires --"},{"time":32520,"text":"acute respiratory infections\ncaused by this."},{"time":36040,"text":"Can you believe that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37880,"text":"I find this shocking\nand somewhat appalling."},{"time":41160,"text":"Can't we make\ncleaner burning cooking fuels?"},{"time":43800,"text":"Can't we make better stoves?"},{"time":45760,"text":"How is it that this can lead\nto over two million deaths every year?"},{"time":49800,"text":"I know Bill Joy was talking to you\nabout the wonders of carbon nanotubes,"},{"time":54160,"text":"so I'm going to talk to you\nabout the wonders of carbon macro-tubes,"},{"time":58000,"text":"which is charcoal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":61240,"text":"So this is a picture of rural Haiti."},{"time":63440,"text":"Haiti is now 98 percent deforested."},{"time":66760,"text":"You'll see scenes like this\nall over the island."},{"time":69880,"text":"It leads to all sorts\nof environmental problems"},{"time":72680,"text":"and problems that affect people\nthroughout the nation."},{"time":76960,"text":"A couple years ago\nthere was severe flooding"},{"time":79040,"text":"that led to thousands of deaths --"},{"time":80684,"text":"that's directly attributable to the fact"},{"time":82640,"text":"that there are no trees on the hills\nto stabilize the soil."},{"time":85640,"text":"So the rains come --"},{"time":86920,"text":"they go down the rivers\nand the flooding happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90440,"text":"Now one of the reasons\nwhy there are so few trees is this:"},{"time":93920,"text":"people need to cook,"},{"time":95320,"text":"and they harvest wood\nand they make charcoal in order to do it."},{"time":99440,"text":"It's not that people are ignorant\nto the environmental damage."},{"time":102369,"text":"They know perfectly well,\nbut they have no other choice."},{"time":105013,"text":"Fossil fuels are not available,"},{"time":107040,"text":"and solar energy doesn't cook the way\nthat they like their food prepared."},{"time":111960,"text":"And so this is what they do."},{"time":114120,"text":"You'll find families like this who go out\ninto the forest to find a tree,"},{"time":118320,"text":"cut it down and make charcoal out of it."},{"time":122440,"text":"So not surprisingly,"},{"time":123680,"text":"there's a lot of effort that's been done\nto look at alternative cooking fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129360,"text":"About four years ago, I took\na team of students down to Haiti"},{"time":132440,"text":"and we worked with\nPeace Corps volunteers there."},{"time":134880,"text":"This is one such volunteer"},{"time":136320,"text":"and this is a device that he had built\nin the village where he worked."},{"time":139960,"text":"And the idea was\nthat you could take waste paper;"},{"time":142640,"text":"you could compress it"},{"time":143880,"text":"and make briquettes\nthat could be used for fuel."},{"time":146560,"text":"But this device was very slow."},{"time":148600,"text":"So our engineering students\nwent to work on it"},{"time":151720,"text":"and with some very simple changes,"},{"time":153840,"text":"they were able to triple\nthe throughput of this device."},{"time":156920,"text":"So you could imagine\nthey were very excited about it."},{"time":159480,"text":"And they took the briquettes back to MIT\nso that they could test them."},{"time":164000,"text":"And one of the things\nthat they found was they didn't burn."},{"time":168280,"text":"So it was a little\ndiscouraging to the students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172640,"text":"And in fact, if you look closely,"},{"time":175040,"text":"right here you can see\nit says, \"US Peace Corps.\""},{"time":178640,"text":"As it turns out, there actually wasn't\nany waste paper in this village."},{"time":182480,"text":"And while it was a good use\nof government paperwork"},{"time":185720,"text":"for this volunteer to bring it\nback with him to his village,"},{"time":188649,"text":"it was 800 kilometers away."},{"time":190760,"text":"And so we thought perhaps\nthere might be a better way"},{"time":193680,"text":"to come up with\nan alternative cooking fuel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196640,"text":"What we wanted to do\nis we wanted to make a fuel"},{"time":198920,"text":"that used something that was\nreadily available on the local level."},{"time":202280,"text":"You see these all over Haiti as well."},{"time":204080,"text":"They're small-scale sugar mills."},{"time":205840,"text":"And the waste product from them"},{"time":207360,"text":"after you extract the juice\nfrom the sugarcane"},{"time":209800,"text":"is called \"bagasse.\""},{"time":211360,"text":"It has no other use."},{"time":212600,"text":"It has no nutritional value,\nso they don't feed it to the animals."},{"time":215920,"text":"It just sits in a pile near the sugar mill\nuntil eventually they burn it."},{"time":221040,"text":"What we wanted to do was\nwe wanted to find a way"},{"time":223360,"text":"to harness this waste resource\nand turn it into a fuel"},{"time":226360,"text":"that would be something\nthat people could easily cook with,"},{"time":229360,"text":"something like charcoal."},{"time":231600,"text":"So over the next couple of years,"},{"time":233240,"text":"students and I worked\nto develop a process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236920,"text":"So you start with the bagasse,\nand then you take a very simple kiln"},{"time":240760,"text":"that you can make out of\na waste fifty five-gallon oil drum."},{"time":243960,"text":"After some time, after setting it on fire,"},{"time":246280,"text":"you seal it to restrict the oxygen\nthat goes into the kiln,"},{"time":250280,"text":"and then you end up\nwith this carbonized material here."},{"time":254080,"text":"However, you can't burn this."},{"time":255680,"text":"It's too fine and it burns too quickly\nto be useful for cooking."},{"time":260399,"text":"So we had to try to find a way\nto form it into useful briquettes."},{"time":264680,"text":"And conveniently,\none of my students was from Ghana,"},{"time":268120,"text":"and he remembered a dish his mom\nused to make for him called \"kokonte,\""},{"time":271478,"text":"which is a very sticky porridge\nmade out of the cassava root."},{"time":274960,"text":"And so what we did was we looked,"},{"time":276560,"text":"and we found that cassava\nis indeed grown in Haiti,"},{"time":279680,"text":"under the name of \"manioc.\""},{"time":281840,"text":"In fact, it's grown all over the world --"},{"time":283817,"text":"yucca, tapioca, manioc, cassava,\nit's all the same thing --"},{"time":286920,"text":"a very starchy root vegetable."},{"time":289040,"text":"And you can make a very thick,\nsticky porridge out of it,"},{"time":292280,"text":"which you can use to bind together\nthe charcoal briquettes."},{"time":296440,"text":"So we did this. We went down to Haiti."},{"time":299640,"text":"These are the graduates\nof the first Ecole de Charbon,"},{"time":302320,"text":"or Charcoal Institute."},{"time":304040,"text":"And these --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306520,"text":"That's right. So I'm actually\nan instructor at MIT as well as CIT."},{"time":312520,"text":"And these are the briquettes that we made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316040,"text":"Now I'm going to take you\nto a different continent."},{"time":319320,"text":"This is India"},{"time":320560,"text":"and this is the most commonly used\ncooking fuel in India."},{"time":323800,"text":"It's cow dung."},{"time":325200,"text":"And more than in Haiti,\nthis produces really smoky fires,"},{"time":329400,"text":"and this is where you see\nthe health impacts"},{"time":331880,"text":"of cooking with cow dung\nand biomass as a fuel."},{"time":336600,"text":"Kids and women\nare especially affected by it,"},{"time":338840,"text":"because they're the ones\nwho are around the cooking fires."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"So we wanted to see"},{"time":343240,"text":"if we could introduce\nthis charcoal-making technology there."},{"time":346760,"text":"Well, unfortunately,\nthey didn't have sugarcane"},{"time":349200,"text":"and they didn't have cassava,"},{"time":350605,"text":"but that didn't stop us."},{"time":352400,"text":"What we did was we found what were\nthe locally available sources of biomass."},{"time":356240,"text":"And there was wheat straw\nand there was rice straw in this area."},{"time":359640,"text":"And what we could use as a binder\nwas actually small amounts of cow manure,"},{"time":363280,"text":"which they used ordinarily for their fuel."},{"time":366960,"text":"And we did side-by-side tests,"},{"time":369160,"text":"and here you can see\nthe charcoal briquettes"},{"time":371760,"text":"and here the cow dung."},{"time":373000,"text":"And you can see that it's a lot cleaner\nburning of a cooking fuel."},{"time":376280,"text":"And in fact, it heats the water\na lot more quickly."},{"time":378880,"text":"And so we were very happy, thus far."},{"time":381200,"text":"But one of the things that we found"},{"time":382920,"text":"was when we did side-by-side\ncomparisons with wood charcoal,"},{"time":385760,"text":"it didn't burn as long."},{"time":387400,"text":"And the briquettes crumbled a little bit"},{"time":389329,"text":"and we lost energy as they fell apart\nas they were cooking."},{"time":392520,"text":"So we wanted to try to find a way\nto make a stronger briquette"},{"time":395760,"text":"so that we could compete with\nwood charcoal in the markets in Haiti."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400320,"text":"So we went back to MIT,"},{"time":402360,"text":"we took out the Instron machine"},{"time":404600,"text":"and we figured out\nwhat sort of forces you needed"},{"time":407320,"text":"in order to compress\na briquette to the level"},{"time":409440,"text":"that you actually are getting\nimproved performance out of it?"},{"time":412960,"text":"And at the same time that we had\nstudents in the lab looking at this,"},{"time":416280,"text":"we also had community partners in Haiti\nworking to develop the process,"},{"time":423240,"text":"to improve it and make it more accessible\nto people in the villages there."},{"time":429160,"text":"And after some time,"},{"time":430400,"text":"we developed a low-cost press\nthat allows you to produce charcoal,"},{"time":435240,"text":"which actually now burns not only --"},{"time":438642,"text":"actually, it burns longer,\ncleaner than wood charcoal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442400,"text":"So now we're in a situation\nwhere we have a product,"},{"time":444960,"text":"which is actually better than what\nyou can buy in Haiti in the marketplace,"},{"time":449280,"text":"which is a very wonderful place to be."},{"time":453960,"text":"In Haiti alone, about 30 million trees\nare cut down every year."},{"time":458720,"text":"There's a possibility\nof this being implemented"},{"time":461240,"text":"and saving a good portion of those."},{"time":463560,"text":"In addition, the revenue generated\nfrom that charcoal is 260 million dollars."},{"time":470000,"text":"That's an awful lot\nfor a country like Haiti --"},{"time":472560,"text":"with a population of eight million"},{"time":474440,"text":"and an average income\nof less than 400 dollars."},{"time":478680,"text":"So this is where we're also moving ahead\nwith our charcoal project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482560,"text":"And one of the things\nthat I think is also interesting,"},{"time":485240,"text":"is I have a friend up at UC Berkeley\nwho's been doing risk analysis."},{"time":489560,"text":"And he's looked at the problem\nof the health impacts"},{"time":492640,"text":"of burning wood versus charcoal."},{"time":494760,"text":"And he's found that worldwide,\nyou could prevent a million deaths"},{"time":498880,"text":"switching from wood\nto charcoal as a cooking fuel."},{"time":501880,"text":"That's remarkable,"},{"time":503120,"text":"but up until now, there weren't ways\nto do it without cutting down trees."},{"time":506600,"text":"But now we have a way"},{"time":507840,"text":"that's using an agricultural\nwaste material to create a cooking fuel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511960,"text":"One of the really exciting things, though,"},{"time":514000,"text":"is something that came out of the trip\nthat I took to Ghana just last month."},{"time":517596,"text":"And I think it's the coolest thing,"},{"time":521039,"text":"and it's even lower tech\nthan what you just saw,"},{"time":523303,"text":"if you can imagine such a thing."},{"time":525360,"text":"Here it is."},{"time":526600,"text":"So what is this?"},{"time":528480,"text":"This is corncobs turned into charcoal."},{"time":531080,"text":"And the beauty of this is\nthat you don't need to form briquettes --"},{"time":534247,"text":"it comes ready made."},{"time":535600,"text":"This is my $100 laptop, right here."},{"time":538480,"text":"And actually, like Nick,\nI brought samples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":543760,"text":"So we can pass these around."},{"time":547520,"text":"They're fully functional,\nfield-tested, ready to roll out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551628,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":555520,"text":"And I think one of the things"},{"time":557040,"text":"which is also remarkable\nabout this technology,"},{"time":561280,"text":"is that the technology\ntransfer is so easy."},{"time":564080,"text":"Compared to the sugarcane charcoal,"},{"time":566240,"text":"where we have to teach people\nhow to form it into briquettes"},{"time":569080,"text":"and you have the extra step\nof cooking the binder,"},{"time":571520,"text":"this comes pre-briquetted."},{"time":573120,"text":"And this is about the most exciting\nthing in my life right now,"},{"time":576097,"text":"which is perhaps\na sad commentary on my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581600,"text":"But once you see it,\nlike you guys in the front row --"},{"time":584160,"text":"All right, yeah, OK."},{"time":585400,"text":"So anyway --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588680,"text":"Here it is."},{"time":589920,"text":"And this is, I think, a perfect example"},{"time":592400,"text":"of what Robert Wright was talking about\nin those non-zero-sum things."},{"time":597640,"text":"So not only do you have health benefits,"},{"time":600160,"text":"you have environmental benefits."},{"time":602320,"text":"But this is one\nof the incredibly rare situations"},{"time":606160,"text":"where you also have economic benefits."},{"time":608520,"text":"People can make their own cooking fuel\nfrom waste products."},{"time":611600,"text":"They can generate income from this."},{"time":613640,"text":"They can save the money\nthat they were going to spend on charcoal"},{"time":616800,"text":"and they can produce excess\nand sell it in the market"},{"time":619301,"text":"to people who aren't making their own."},{"time":621280,"text":"It's really rare\nthat you don't have trade-offs"},{"time":623600,"text":"between health and economics,\nor environment and economics."},{"time":626840,"text":"So this is a project\nthat I just find extremely exciting"},{"time":630600,"text":"and I'm really looking forward\nto see where it takes us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638120,"text":"So when we talk about, now,\nthe future we will create,"},{"time":641640,"text":"one of the things\nthat I think is necessary"},{"time":643680,"text":"is to have a very clear vision\nof the world that we live in."},{"time":648160,"text":"And now, I don't actually mean\nthe world that we live in."},{"time":651920,"text":"I mean the world where women\nspend two to three hours everyday"},{"time":656040,"text":"grinding grain for their families to eat."},{"time":659960,"text":"I mean the world\nwhere advanced building materials"},{"time":662360,"text":"means cement roofing tiles\nthat are made by hand,"},{"time":665800,"text":"and where, when you work 10 hours a day,"},{"time":667960,"text":"you're still only earning\n60 dollars in a month."},{"time":672320,"text":"I mean the world"},{"time":673560,"text":"where women and children spend\n40 billion hours a year fetching water."},{"time":680520,"text":"That's as if the entire workforce\nof the state of California"},{"time":684280,"text":"worked full time for a year\ndoing nothing but fetching water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688800,"text":"It's a place where,\nfor example, if this were India,"},{"time":693160,"text":"in this room, only three of us\nwould have a car."},{"time":696360,"text":"If this were Afghanistan,"},{"time":697600,"text":"only one person in this room\nwould know how the use the Internet."},{"time":701240,"text":"If this were Zambia --"},{"time":703520,"text":"300 of you would be farmers,"},{"time":706240,"text":"100 of you would have AIDS or HIV."},{"time":709400,"text":"And more than half of you would be living\non less than a dollar a day."},{"time":714280,"text":"These are the issues that we\nneed to come up with solutions for."},{"time":719040,"text":"These are the issues that\nwe need to be training our engineers,"},{"time":722920,"text":"our designers, our business people,\nour entrepreneurs to be facing."},{"time":727280,"text":"These are the solutions\nthat we need to find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"I have a few areas that I believe\nare especially important that we address."},{"time":736200,"text":"One of them is creating technologies"},{"time":738280,"text":"to promote micro-finance\nand micro-enterprise,"},{"time":741320,"text":"so that people who are living\nbelow the poverty line"},{"time":744200,"text":"can find a way to move out --"},{"time":745760,"text":"and that they're not doing it"},{"time":747165,"text":"using the same traditional\nbasket making, poultry rearing, etc."},{"time":750800,"text":"But there are new technologies\nand new products"},{"time":753015,"text":"that they can make on a small scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755800,"text":"The next thing I believe"},{"time":757040,"text":"is that we need to create\ntechnologies for poor farmers"},{"time":761440,"text":"to add value to their own crops."},{"time":764600,"text":"And we need to rethink\nour development strategies,"},{"time":767280,"text":"so that we're not promoting\neducational campaigns"},{"time":770560,"text":"to get them to stop being farmers,"},{"time":772960,"text":"but rather to stop being poor farmers."},{"time":775760,"text":"And we need to think\nabout how we can do that effectively."},{"time":779560,"text":"We need to work with the people\nin these communities"},{"time":782240,"text":"and give them the resources\nand the tools that they need"},{"time":785120,"text":"to solve their own problems."},{"time":786840,"text":"That's the best way to do it."},{"time":788245,"text":"We shouldn't be doing it from outside."},{"time":790560,"text":"So we need to create this future,\nand we need to start doing it now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795240,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796480,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":801760,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you, incredible."},{"time":804320,"text":"Stay here."},{"time":806360,"text":"Tell us -- just while we see\nif someone has a question --"},{"time":809280,"text":"just tell us about one of the other things\nthat you've worked on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812720,"text":"Amy Smith: Some of the other\nthings we're working on"},{"time":815240,"text":"are ways to do low-cost\nwater quality testing,"},{"time":817441,"text":"so that communities can maintain\ntheir own water systems,"},{"time":820200,"text":"know when they're working,\nknow when they treat them, etc."},{"time":822939,"text":"We're also looking at low-cost\nwater-treatment systems."},{"time":825600,"text":"One of the really exciting things\nis looking at solar water disinfection"},{"time":829005,"text":"and improving the ability\nto be able to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832320,"text":"CA: What's the bottleneck\npreventing this stuff getting from scale?"},{"time":836280,"text":"Do you need to find entrepreneurs,\nor venture capitalists,"},{"time":839560,"text":"or what do you need to take\nwhat you've got and get it to scale?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":844440,"text":"AS: I think it's large numbers\nof people moving it forward."},{"time":847234,"text":"It's a difficult thing --"},{"time":848457,"text":"it's a marketplace\nwhich is very fragmented"},{"time":850488,"text":"and a consumer population with no income."},{"time":852720,"text":"So you can't use the same models\nthat you use in the United States"},{"time":856000,"text":"for making things move forward."},{"time":857560,"text":"And we're a pretty small staff,"},{"time":859600,"text":"which is me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":862840,"text":"So, you know,\nI do what I can with the students."},{"time":865103,"text":"We have 30 students a year\ngo out into the field"},{"time":867366,"text":"and try to implement this\nand move it forward."},{"time":869840,"text":"The other thing is you have to do things\nwith a long time frame,"},{"time":873360,"text":"as, you know, you can't expect to get\nsomething done in a year or two years;"},{"time":877320,"text":"you have to be looking\nfive or 10 years ahead."},{"time":879487,"text":"But I think with the vision to do that,\nwe can move forward."}]}]}